# Project: [Your Project Name]

## Tech Stack
- Language: Python 3.11
- Framework: FastAPI
- Database: PostgreSQL
- Testing: pytest

## Commands
```bash
# Run tests
pytest

# Run with coverage
pytest --cov=src --cov-report=html

# Start dev server
uvicorn src.main:app --reload

# Database migrations
alembic upgrade head
```

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── domain/        # Business entities, no dependencies
├── application/   # Use cases, depends on domain
├── infrastructure/# Database, external APIs
└── presentation/  # API endpoints, controllers
```

## Rules
- Dependencies point inward (Clean Architecture)
- No `except: pass` - all errors must be explicit
- New code needs tests (target: 80% coverage)
- All comments and docs in English

## Conventions
- File naming: snake_case.py
- Class naming: PascalCase
- Function naming: snake_case
- API routes: kebab-case (/user-profile)

## Before Implementing
- Check if similar code exists (avoid duplication)
- Run existing tests to ensure baseline works

## After Implementing
- Run tests: `pytest`
- Check for linting issues: `ruff check src/`
